service notes: Title: Recurring Camshaft Position Sensor Issues in 2022 Hyundai Tucson

Issue:
- Vehicle presenting P0342 code
- Extended engine startup time
- Low voltage detected on Camshaft Position Sensor signal circuit
- Second occurrence of the same issue (previous replacement in April 2025)

Diagnostic Steps:
1. Scanned and confirmed P0342 code (Camshaft Position Sensor Circuit Low Input Bank 1)
2. Verified low voltage on signal circuit
3. Checked service history revealing previous sensor replacement

Repair Solution:
1. Replaced Bank 1 Camshaft Position Sensor
2. Used Bosch replacement part (P/N: 393503E110)
3. Verified proper operation after replacement

Technical Notes:
- Recurring issue within short timeframe suggests possible underlying causes
- Recommend monitoring for voltage irregularities in the circuit
- Consider checking wiring harness integrity in future occurrences

Parts Used:
- Bosch Camshaft Position Sensor (P/N: 393503E110) 
